{
  "texts": [
    "The graph pooling computing framework is a tool and platform carefully designed for processing deep learning tasks on graph-structured data.",
    "These frameworks greatly improve the performance and efficiency of deep learning tasks on graph data by integrating efficient graph pooling algorithms.",
    "Using these frameworks, researchers and developers can easily implement a variety of graph pooling methods to build more powerful, accurate, and efficient deep learning models on graph data.",
    "The graph pooling computing framework not only simplifies the implementation process of graph pooling technology but also accelerates the training and inference speed of the model, providing strong support for research and application in the field of graph neural networks.",
    "Graph computing frameworks provide diverse tools and platforms for the processing and analysis of graph data, and these frameworks significantly improve the efficiency and performance of performing deep learning tasks on graph data by integrating efficient graph pooling algorithms (Zhao et al. 2022)."
  ]
}